answers.answer: Is it your upper back or lower back hurting?

Your headache is primarily due to pre eclampsia ...you need to get your B.p checked ...it can affect the baby too...dont delay...Now difficulty breathing can be due to edema..i.e swelling , which is again bcz of pre eclampsia. Heartburn can be due to it or mightily not be. ..try taking antacids to relieve it.

It's all over my back and belly. I took some Tylenol and my headache has subsided but it's still there.. my legs and feet are even hurting. Idk it's like my whole body aches. it doesn't feel like the flu or anything. I just have zero energy and am achy.

Idk what is going on :( I see my dr Wed so I am trying to hold off until then.. I have had high blood pressure and a lot of swelling so idk if the pains are related to preeclampsia or what.
